24/11/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A total of 1.6m square metres in the former crisis regions have been cleared of mines, according to the Skopje-based NGO Civil.
On Tuesday (23 November), the group presented a report titled "Five Years of Action against the Mines", which concludes that Macedonia has managed to recover relatively quickly from the 2001 security crisis.
According to the publication, there have been no new victims of mine explosions in the country during 2004.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 24/11/04)
